The paper deals with formal languages and automata theory, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The concept of discounted summation is commonly used in finance and economics, which could also place the paper under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the algebraic operations of min, max, addition, and subtraction, which could place it under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper deals with determinization and closure properties, which are important topics in Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Discrete Structures (cs.DS).
